<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="010" project="code-quality-and-assurance-r2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Decompose OfficeService.cs into 4 Focused Services</title>
    <phase>2: Backend Structural Decomposition</phase>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-hours>8</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>001</dependencies>
    <blocks>013</blocks>
    <tags>refactoring, dotnet, bff-api</tags>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Decompose OfficeService.cs (2,907 lines) into a thin orchestrator plus 4 focused services, each
    with a single well-defined responsibility. Also delete the obsolete SimulateJobProgressAsync
    method (319 lines of dead code). After extraction, OfficeService.SaveAsync becomes a thin
    orchestrator that delegates to the 4 injected services. Register all new services in the
    existing OfficeModule.cs following the AddXxxModule pattern.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET developer specializing in SOLID principles and service decomposition</role>

  <goal>
    OfficeService.cs is reduced to fewer than 500 lines and contains only orchestration logic.
    Four new focused service files exist, each under 500 lines, each with a single responsibility.
    SimulateJobProgressAsync is deleted. All new services are registered in OfficeModule.cs.
    dotnet build passes with zero errors.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      OfficeService.cs has grown to 2,907 lines and violates the Single Responsibility Principle.
      It handles email enrichment (Graph + MimeKit), Dataverse CRUD, Service Bus queuing, and SPE
      storage upload all in one class. This makes it untestable in isolation, increases constructor
      parameter count, and inflates cognitive complexity. The goal of Phase 2 is to decompose God
      classes into focused services so that each class can be reasoned about, tested, and modified
      independently. Additionally, SimulateJobProgressAsync is marked [Obsolete] and accounts for
      319 lines that are never called in production; deleting it reduces surface area and noise.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Office/OfficeService.cs (modify — primary target)</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/OfficeModule.cs (modify — register new services)</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Office/OfficeEmailEnricher.cs (create)</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Office/OfficeDocumentPersistence.cs (create)</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Office/OfficeJobQueue.cs (create)</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Office/OfficeStorageUploader.cs (create)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-007">
      Never leak Graph SDK types (GraphServiceClient, DriveItem, etc.) above the SpeFileStore
      facade. OfficeStorageUploader must call SpeFileStore methods only — no direct Graph SDK calls.
    </constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">
      Register services as concrete types unless a seam is required for testing. New services must
      be registered inside OfficeModule.cs using the existing AddOfficeModule extension method
      pattern. Total non-framework DI registrations must remain at or below 15.
    </constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-007.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-010.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">
      Read OfficeService.cs in full. Catalog every method, its line range, its dependencies
      (which injected fields it uses), and which of the 4 responsibility groups it belongs to:
      (a) email enrichment, (b) Dataverse persistence, (c) Service Bus queuing, (d) SPE upload.
      Record the catalog in a comment block at the top of your working notes before writing any
      new files.
    </step>
    <step order="2">
      Create OfficeEmailEnricher.cs in src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Office/.
      Move into it: EnrichEmailFromGraphAsync, EnrichAttachmentFromGraphAsync,
      BuildEmlFromMetadata, GenerateEmlFileName, SanitizeFileName (~400 lines).
      Constructor dependencies: IGraphClientFactory, ILogger&lt;OfficeEmailEnricher&gt;.
      Keep the same method signatures so call sites in OfficeService need no changes yet.
    </step>
    <step order="3">
      Create OfficeDocumentPersistence.cs in src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Office/.
      Move into it: CreateDocumentWithSpePointersAsync, UpdateJobStatusInDataverseAsync,
      CheckForExistingJobAsync, GenerateDataverseUrl, and all MapDataverse* helper methods
      (~300 lines).
      Constructor dependencies: IDataverseService, ILogger&lt;OfficeDocumentPersistence&gt;.
    </step>
    <step order="4">
      Create OfficeJobQueue.cs in src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Office/.
      Move into it: QueueUploadFinalizationAsync, GetMimeType (~150 lines).
      Constructor dependencies: ServiceBusClient, ServiceBusOptions (IOptions&lt;ServiceBusOptions&gt;),
      ILogger&lt;OfficeJobQueue&gt;.
    </step>
    <step order="5">
      Create OfficeStorageUploader.cs in src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Office/.
      Move into it: UploadToSpeAsync (~50 lines).
      Constructor dependency: SpeFileStore, ILogger&lt;OfficeStorageUploader&gt;.
      Confirm no raw Graph SDK types are used — only SpeFileStore methods (ADR-007).
    </step>
    <step order="6">
      Update OfficeService.cs constructor. Replace raw dependencies absorbed by the 4 new services
      with injected instances of OfficeEmailEnricher, OfficeDocumentPersistence, OfficeJobQueue,
      and OfficeStorageUploader.
    </step>
    <step order="7">
      Refactor OfficeService.SaveAsync to delegate to the injected services rather than calling
      the moved methods directly. Ensure all call sites within OfficeService are updated.
      GetJobStatusAsync may stay in OfficeService or be moved to a thin OfficeJobStatusService
      if it makes the class cleaner — document the decision in a code comment.
    </step>
    <step order="8">
      Delete SimulateJobProgressAsync and any private helpers called exclusively by it.
      Confirm with a grep that no other code in the solution calls SimulateJobProgressAsync
      before deleting.
    </step>
    <step order="9">
      Register the 4 new services in OfficeModule.cs using concrete registration
      (services.AddScoped&lt;OfficeEmailEnricher&gt;(), etc.) following ADR-010.
    </step>
    <step order="10">
      Run dotnet build from the repository root. Fix any compilation errors before proceeding.
      Do not proceed to step 11 until the build is green.
    </step>
    <step order="11">
      Verify OfficeService.cs is under 500 lines (run: wc -l on the file or count manually).
      If it still exceeds 500 lines, identify remaining candidates to extract and extract them.
    </step>
    <step order="12">
      Update projects/code-quality-and-assurance-r2/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md — mark task 010 complete.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <output type="file">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Office/OfficeEmailEnricher.cs</output>
    <output type="file">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Office/OfficeDocumentPersistence.cs</output>
    <output type="file">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Office/OfficeJobQueue.cs</output>
    <output type="file">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Office/OfficeStorageUploader.cs</output>
    <output type="file">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Office/OfficeService.cs (modified)</output>
    <output type="file">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/OfficeModule.cs (modified)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>OfficeService.cs is fewer than 500 lines after decomposition</criterion>
    <criterion>Four new focused service files are created: OfficeEmailEnricher.cs, OfficeDocumentPersistence.cs, OfficeJobQueue.cs, OfficeStorageUploader.cs</criterion>
    <criterion>SimulateJobProgressAsync and its exclusive helpers are deleted from the codebase</criterion>
    <criterion>All 4 new services are registered in OfficeModule.cs</criterion>
    <criterion>dotnet build passes with zero errors across the entire solution</criterion>
    <criterion>OfficeStorageUploader contains no direct Graph SDK type usage (ADR-007 compliance)</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
